---
title: "_applyAllowlistedSelectorsUpdates (WorkflowRouter)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_wf: check workflowId allowlisted
    q_check_wf --> q_revert_wf: !s_allowlistedWorkflowIds.contains(workflowId)
    q_revert_wf --> [*]: revert WorkflowIdNotAllowlisted(workflowId)
    q_check_wf --> q_check_target: workflowId is allowlisted
    q_check_target --> q_revert_target: !allowlistedTargets.contains(target)
    q_revert_target --> [*]: revert TargetNotAllowlisted(workflowId, target)
    q_check_target --> q_check_empty: target is allowlisted
    q_check_empty --> q_revert_empty: removes.length == 0 AND adds.length == 0
    q_revert_empty --> [*]: revert EmptyList()
    q_check_empty --> q_iter_removes: at least one list non-empty
    q_iter_removes --> q_remove_sel: i < removes.length
    q_remove_sel --> q_try_remove: selector = removes[i]
    q_try_remove --> q_revert_sel: !allowlistedSelectors[target].remove(bytes32(selector))
    q_revert_sel --> [*]: revert SelectorNotAllowlisted(workflowId, target, selector)
    q_try_remove --> q_emit_remove: remove succeeded
    q_emit_remove --> q_iter_removes: emit SelectorRemovedFromAllowlist(workflowId, target, selector); i++
    q_iter_removes --> q_iter_adds: i >= removes.length
    q_iter_adds --> q_add_sel: i < adds.length
    q_add_sel --> q_check_zero: selector = adds[i]
    q_check_zero --> q_revert_zero: selector == bytes4(0)
    q_revert_zero --> [*]: revert InvalidZeroValue()
    q_check_zero --> q_try_add: selector != bytes4(0)
    q_try_add --> q_emit_add: allowlistedSelectors[target].add(bytes32(selector)) returns true
    q_emit_add --> q_iter_adds: emit SelectorAllowlisted(workflowId, target, selector); i++
    q_try_add --> q_iter_adds: add returns false (already exists, no emit); i++
    q_iter_adds --> [*]: i >= adds.length

    note right of q_check_wf
        INV-001: workflowId must be allowlisted
        INV-002: target must be allowlisted for the workflowId
        INV-003: removing a non-existent selector reverts
        INV-004: adding a duplicate selector is a no-op (no event emitted)
        INV-005: zero selector cannot be added
    end note
